---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — System Report" description="System Report delivers in-depth analysis and expert commentary on the tech stories that matter.">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-6">
      About System Report
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray dark:prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:font-serif prose-a:text-blue-600 dark:prose-a:text-blue-400">
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        System Report is a tech news publication focused on delivering clear, well-researched analysis of the stories shaping the technology industry. We cut through the noise to surface what actually matters.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Cover</h2>

      <p>We cover the full spectrum of the tech landscape, including:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Silicon & Hardware</strong> — Chip architecture, device launches, and the semiconductor supply chain</li>
        <li><strong>Artificial Intelligence</strong> — Model breakthroughs, enterprise adoption, and the societal impact of AI</li>
        <li><strong>Software & Platforms</strong> — Developer tools, cloud infrastructure, and the evolving platform economy</li>
        <li><strong>Policy & Regulation</strong> — Digital governance, antitrust, and the global regulatory landscape</li>
        <li><strong>Security & Privacy</strong> — Threat intelligence, vulnerability disclosures, and data protection</li>
        <li><strong>Startups & Venture</strong> — Funding rounds, market shifts, and emerging technology companies</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Approach</h2>

      <p>
        Every article on System Report is an original piece. We don't rehash press releases or rewrite headlines. Our editorial process involves reading multiple primary sources covering the same story, distilling the key facts, and producing a comprehensive take that gives readers a complete picture in a single read.
      </p>

      <p>
        We believe in quantity <em>and</em> quality. Our publication cadence is frequent, but every piece meets the same editorial standard: accurate, well-sourced, and worth your time.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Standards</h2>

      <div class="not-prose">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-8">
          <div class="p-5 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1">Accuracy First</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Every claim is cross-referenced against multiple sources before publication.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1">No Clickbait</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Headlines tell you what happened. We don't hide the story behind a question mark.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1">No Paywall</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">All content is free to read. High-quality journalism shouldn't be gated.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1">Fast & Private</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Static architecture means instant page loads and no tracking cookies.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Contact</h2>

      <p>
        Have a tip, a correction, or a question? Email us at <a href="mailto:contact@systemreport.net">contact@systemreport.net</a> or visit our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
